<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1447,1680]" box="[160,227,1447,1472]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,227,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">Notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[160,1156,1447,1680]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">
In the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Cavallo P &amp; Ferretti N" box="[632,919,1483,1507]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951" pagination="873 - 887" refId="ref23215" refString="Cavallo P, Ferretti N. 2015. The first Hapalotremus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Theraphosidae) from Argentina: description and natural history of Hapalotremus martinorum sp. nov. J Nat Hist. 49 (15 - 16): 873 - 887." type="journal article" year="2015">Cavallo and Ferretti 2015</bibRefCitation>
), the ventral crest of the prolateral inferior keel was described as a subapical keel due to its triangular shape and position. However, a more detailed examination of the male 
<typeStatus box="[949,1049,1552,1576]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">holotype</typeStatus>
and the comparison with the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[603,756,1587,1611]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,756,1587,1611]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">Hapalotremus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
led us to identify a continuous 
<collectionCode box="[1135,1156,1587,1611]" country="Russia" name="Paleontological Institute" pageId="25" pageNumber="1951">PI</collectionCode>
very well-developed along the embolus having a ventral expansion or crest, as found in all known species.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747299" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4747299" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747299/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" startId="26.[160,225,1303,1326]" targetBox="[163,1150,142,1272]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1157,1303,1385]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,268,1303,1326]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">Figure 22.</emphasis>
(a–e) 
<taxonomicName authority="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West, 2018" authorityName="Ferretti &amp; Cavallo &amp; Chaparro &amp; Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Seimon &amp; West" authorityYear="2018" box="[338,557,1303,1326]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chasqui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[338,557,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">Hapalotremus chasqui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,654,1303,1326]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female paratype (MACN-Ar 35596). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (d) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,1461,1659]" box="[160,394,1461,1486]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,394,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">Amended diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1155,1461,1659]" lastBlockId="28.[160,1156,1176,1443]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="1954" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Cavallo and Ferretti" authorityYear="2015" box="[160,453,1496,1520]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[160,453,1496,1520]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">Hapalotremus martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a distinct green pubescence between the patella and tarsi of legs and on the lateral faces of the abdomen in combination with red setae on the urticating patch (
<figureCitation box="[501,632,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1268,1291]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-72@4.[163,1152,142,1237]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. (a–f) Hapalotremus spp. habitus. (a) Hapalotremus albipes, female. (b) Hapalotremus major, female. (c, d) Hapalotremus martinorum. (c) Male. (d) Female. (e) Hapalotremus chasqui sp. nov., juvenile. (f) Hapalotremus marcapata sp. nov., female. Photos: a: Mauricio Pacheco Suarez; b: Juan Chaparro; c, d: Patricio Cavallo; e: Laura Montes de Oca; f: Josh Richards." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747251/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">Figure 1c, d</figureCitation>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Cavallo and Ferretti" authorityYear="2015" box="[754,914,1565,1589]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[754,914,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[325,433,1600,1624]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipes">
<emphasis box="[325,433,1600,1624]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">H. albipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[494,590,1600,1624]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[494,590,1600,1624]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">H. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a large number of labial cuspules (more than 20), tibia I about 10% longer than metatarsus I (
<figureCitation box="[760,888,1635,1659]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="17.[160,225,859,882]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,142,828]" captionTargetId="figure-273@17.[163,1152,142,828]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 13. (a–i) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype (MLP 19152). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Eyes, dorsal view. (e) Labium and maxillae, ventral view. (f) Tibial apophysis, ventral view. (g) Leg I, lateral view. (h) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (i) Palpal tibia, ventral view. Arrows indicate the rounded process. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747279/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952">
Figure 
<quantity box="[845,888,1635,1659]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="26" pageNumber="1952" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), by having a slightly developed retrolateral rounded process on palpal tibia (
<figureCitation box="[804,948,1614,1638]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="17.[160,225,859,882]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,142,828]" captionTargetId="figure-273@17.[163,1152,142,828]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 13. (a–i) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype (MLP 19152). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Eyes, dorsal view. (e) Labium and maxillae, ventral view. (f) Tibial apophysis, ventral view. (g) Leg I, lateral view. (h) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (i) Palpal tibia, ventral view. Arrows indicate the rounded process. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747279/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">Figure 13h, i</figureCitation>
), unequal sizes of tibial apophysis branches (
<collectionCode box="[467,498,1648,1672]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">PB</collectionCode>
smaller than 
<collectionCode box="[660,691,1648,1672]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">RB</collectionCode>
) (
<figureCitation box="[714,861,1648,1672]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="17.[160,225,859,882]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,142,828]" captionTargetId="figure-273@17.[163,1152,142,828]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 13. (a–i) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype (MLP 19152). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Eyes, dorsal view. (e) Labium and maxillae, ventral view. (f) Tibial apophysis, ventral view. (g) Leg I, lateral view. (h) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (i) Palpal tibia, ventral view. Arrows indicate the rounded process. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747279/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">Figure 13f, g</figureCitation>
) and slower curvature of metatarsus I (
<figureCitation box="[318,441,1683,1707]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="17.[160,225,859,882]" captionTargetBox="[165,1152,142,828]" captionTargetId="figure-273@17.[163,1152,142,828]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 13. (a–i) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype (MLP 19152). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Eyes, dorsal view. (e) Labium and maxillae, ventral view. (f) Tibial apophysis, ventral view. (g) Leg I, lateral view. (h) Palpal tibia, retrolateral view. (i) Palpal tibia, ventral view. Arrows indicate the rounded process. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747279/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">
Figure 
<quantity box="[399,441,1683,1707]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Palpal bulb resembles that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[815,911,1683,1707]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[815,911,1683,1707]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1953">H. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs by the more developed digitiform apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[598,745,1176,1200]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1095,1118]" captionTargetBox="[164,1153,143,1049]" captionTargetId="figure-131@18.[163,1153,142,1065]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype left palpal bulb (MLP 19152). (a) Prolateral view. (b) Retrolateral view. (c) Dorsal view. (d) Ventral view. (e) Embolus showing keels. A, apical keel; AK accessory keel; DA, digitiform apophysis; PI, prolateral inferior keel; PS, prolateral superior keel. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747281/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Figure 14a–d</figureCitation>
) and prolateral keels (
<figureCitation box="[995,1142,1176,1200]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1095,1118]" captionTargetBox="[164,1153,143,1049]" captionTargetId="figure-131@18.[163,1153,142,1065]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype left palpal bulb (MLP 19152). (a) Prolateral view. (b) Retrolateral view. (c) Dorsal view. (d) Ventral view. (e) Embolus showing keels. A, apical keel; AK accessory keel; DA, digitiform apophysis; PI, prolateral inferior keel; PS, prolateral superior keel. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747281/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Figure 14a–d</figureCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Cavallo and Ferretti" authorityYear="2015" box="[290,451,1211,1235]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[290,451,1211,1235]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[861,968,1211,1235]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipes">
<emphasis box="[861,968,1211,1235]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">H. albipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1916" box="[1026,1120,1211,1235]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[1026,1120,1211,1235]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">H. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger number of cuspules on labium (more than 25 cuspules) (
<figureCitation box="[951,1086,1245,1269]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1006,1029]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,975]" captionTargetId="figure-173@19.[163,1152,142,975]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 15. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, female paratype (MLP 19153). (a) Carapace, dorsal view. (b) Sternum, ventral view. (c) Abdomen, dorsal view. (d) Abdomen, ventral view. (e) Abdomen, lateral view. Scale bar: 5 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747283/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Figures 15b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1102,1142,1245,1269]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="20.[160,225,1355,1378]" captionTargetBox="[163,1151,142,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-111@20.[163,1152,142,1324]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 16. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, female paratype (MLP 19153). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (d) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747285/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">16a</figureCitation>
). Additionally, males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Cavallo and Ferretti" authorityYear="2015" box="[421,586,1280,1304]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[421,586,1280,1304]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from all 
<taxonomicName box="[767,1012,1280,1304]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[767,920,1280,1304]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Hapalotremus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an accessory keel (
<collectionCode box="[473,507,1315,1339]" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">AK</collectionCode>
) on palpal embolus located among 
<collectionCode box="[919,940,1315,1339]" country="Russia" name="Paleontological Institute" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">PI</collectionCode>
and A (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1095,1118]" captionTargetBox="[164,1153,143,1049]" captionTargetId="figure-131@18.[163,1153,142,1065]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, male holotype left palpal bulb (MLP 19152). (a) Prolateral view. (b) Retrolateral view. (c) Dorsal view. (d) Ventral view. (e) Embolus showing keels. A, apical keel; AK accessory keel; DA, digitiform apophysis; PI, prolateral inferior keel; PS, prolateral superior keel. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747281" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747281/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Figure 14a, e</figureCitation>
). Also, females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Cavallo and Ferretti" authorityYear="2015" box="[382,544,1349,1373]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hapalotremus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinorum">
<emphasis box="[382,544,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">H. martinorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be characterized by the shape of the spermathecae, with basal portion wider than apical, apical lateral projections slightly developed and protrude from the apical median region (
<figureCitation box="[684,804,1419,1443]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="20.[160,225,1355,1378]" captionTargetBox="[163,1151,142,1324]" captionTargetId="figure-111@20.[163,1152,142,1324]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 16. (a–e) Hapalotremus martinorum, female paratype (MLP 19153). (a) Labium, ventral view. (b) Eyes, dorsal view. (c) Tarsus IV, prolateral view. (d) Tarsus IV, ventral view. (e) Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm. Photos: Nelson Ferretti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4747285/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="1954">Figure 16e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
